description: Virgil tells Frieda how he became Static and why he couldn't fight Biz Money B (Hot-Streak). He describes how Biz Money B had bullied him when he first met Frieda which caused him to get a gun from Larry and head to the big bang. Virgil had intended to kill Biz Money, but then he realized he wasn't a killer and threw the gun away and had intended to leave, but then they unleashed the gas (Quantum Juice) and Virgil fell unconscious. When he awoke Virgil saw the changes that had begun in the people around him and fled the scene while discovering his own newfound powers. He then trained using these powers and emerged as Static. Static then faces Hot-Streak again and defeats him with ease and later he tries to bring his relation ship with Frieda to a new level, but she turns him down. Tarmack and Holocaust are shown discussing Hot-Streak's defeat and wonder if they should employ Static.
name: Everything but the Girl

description:
Timmorn Yellow Eyes is the chief of the Wolfriders, succeeding Timmain, who withdrew from plot-visibility until ElfQuest #20. He hunts with a wolfpack, but not often with the elf-clan.

As the story unfolds, he becomes more ferral and wolflike than reasoning and elflike. He must withdraw from his role as Chieftain, but before he becomes completely animal, he asks Zarhan Fastfire keeper of The High-Ones' divine talents to marry his daughter Rahnee The She-Wolf.
name: COLORS

description: Rayek is tending the Palace of The High-Ones, which is located under the sea nearby the Wolfriders' forest. He has a terrible reputation since abandoning his people in ElfQuest: Kings of the Broken Wheel. He sets to win his reputation by hunting for the tribe's food. He makes a great stride forward in gaining frienship by bringing down a buck.
name: DAUGHTER'S DAY

description:
This story is set in Sun Village when Suntop and Ember are not yet five years old. They cannot sleep and demand that Cutter tell them a help-sleep story:

In the tale, Skywise dares Cutter to climb up a cliff onto a ledge, where cutter has his first encounter with humans. He meets a benevolent woman who feeds him, and then watches a giant man beat her. He stands up to him, and he chases him to the edge of the cliff, where he has no choice but to face his fear of heights, whereas the man pursues him and dies in a horrific fall.
name: KING OF THE HILL

description:
Cable has made it back to his Swiss Alps residence in the present but Bridge is still hunting him and he's getting closer by the minute. Meanwhile, a group of mercenaries are searching for Deadpool.

Cable and Kane are trapped in a time machine below water and spend most the time talking about their pasts. G. W. searches through Cable's safe house for info. Sinsear is in search of Deadpool. Cable returns to his safe house and G. W. tells Cable he knows were X-Force is.

Synopsis

Having just arrived back in the present, Cable and Garrison find themselves in a very dark Time Displacement chamber. Kane clears up that Cable's base of Graymalkin allowed him to travel anywhere - so what happened this time? Cable doesn't know but tells Kane to settle down so that he can get things sorted out. Kane then rambles about his past; how he joined the military life at age 13 and hasn't much to show for his life. Cable tells Kane that he's found something better than a way out: beer. The two settle down with their drinks and Kane figures that now is a great time to get some answers.

In the Swiss Alps, a man skis towards a house. As he draws closer he trips an alarm. Defenses are raised and the man is shot at while he continues his course towards the house. The defenses ramp up and the man turns on some jets on his skis and launches himself into the home. The defenses immediately cease when the man is recognized by the systems. The home belongs to Cable; the systems are run by the Professor; the man is G.W. Bridge. As a former friend, Bridge is welcomed by the Professor.

In Sarajevo, a lone man named Weasel walks through the war-torn streets while singing his own rendition of a Sinatra song. He is shot at upon entering his safehouse. It's only a warning shot, as Sinsear is there looking for information about Deadpool. Weasel relates that Deadpool hasn't been around for a while since leaving to find his old girlfriend, Copycat. Weasel then starts rambling about how profitable the civil war has been in Sarajevo and Sinsear has to shut him up. Sinsear explains that he needs Deadpool because he is closely associated with someone called "the Other."

Back under the ocean, Cable tells Kane that he's drinking too fast. Kane explains that tight places now get under his skin after being stuck under so much rubble, no thanks to Cable. Changing the subject, Kane asks Cable why he never knew that Stryfe was his twin brother. Cable explains that he's learned that Stryfe is/was not his twin. They are more like odd mirror images of each other. Cable, however, has limited telekinetic abilities while Stryfe could wreak all kinds of havoc with his abilities. Cable believes that Stryfe is the original and that Cable is some kinds of washed-down version, a clone. He figures Stryfe came back in time to kill the parents that somehow end up being Cyclops and Jean Grey. Cable assures Kane that this mission will succeed because he's going to exact whatever revenge Stryfe wanted to exact.

In Cable's chalet in Switzerland, Bridge tries to get a few things straight. Being near Graymalkin when it exploded he thought that Cable's computer system was completely destroyed. The Professor explains that it had merely created as situation in which it would appear that Graymalkin had been destroyed when it had really jettisoned off a few parts and recloaked itself. Bridge then can't believe that after all Cable had put the old Six Pack team through that Bridge was now hanging out with the fabled Professor - a computer system that has made one incredible pot of coffee, at that. Sad, Bridge laments, that this meeting had to occur after Cable's death. Professor then refutes this notion and states that Bridge hangs out for just a little bit longer he may find out the real ending to the fight between Cable and Stryfe.

Back in Sarajevo, Sinsear scans the landscape for any sign of Deadpool. He runs into a band of mercenaries doing the same thing. One of the men asks if Sinsear is also looking to get into the Tolliver Will. Having enough of these men, Sinsear very efficiently kills them with a parabolic slicing blade (a flying razor disc). One man is allowed to live. Having mentioned Tolliver, "the Other," Sinsear asks this man for information.

Underwater, Kane asks how Cable is able to keep going after losing so much in his life. The answer is that if Cable gives up then nothing would have mattered. All the lives lost would have been for nothing. As long as Cable fights, "they" don't win. He then tells Kane to get ready. Cable has had the bunker tapped in to his personal power supply. With the teleporter now ready, Cable and Kane ready themselves for an arrival at the Swiss safehouse. Upon arriving they get the odd surprise of seeing Bridge waiting for them. Cable threatens to kill Bridge then and there but Bridge states that he knows where X-Force is located.
name: Twenty Questions

description: Heat, Part 2 of 4. The heat wave continues as Catman escalates from violent thief to full-fledged serial killer, turning Gotham City into a powder keg about to explode into riots. Gordon struggles with a mayor who uses the killings to prey on racial feelings, and Batman is drawn from the hunt to stop mob violence. Plus, Catwoman tackles Catman alone...with disastrous results.

description:
Adam Warlock is comatose in a far away dimension. His body is discovered by a mystic named Darklore and his companion Meer'Lyn. The Soul Gem awakens and begins to speak with Darklore about his and Adam Warlock's past, all the way up to the Goddess expelling him to this dimension and the damage done to him.

The Soul Gem decides that Darklore would be a far better host and tries to take control of him. But Warlock comes out of his coma and puts the gem back where it belongs. Darklore cannot help Warlock escape but he has something else to show him. It is a hole developing in reality, and only someone with the Reality Gem could be capable of this.

He begins to travel to the one he entrusted with the Reality Gem.

description:
Has Elasti-Girl really returned from the dead? If so, why is she palling around with the Brotherhood of Evil?

Roy Harper's debut as Arsenal!

Firestar then shoots a microwave beam at Carnage and he runs in fear, as Venom tries to get her to cook Carnage until he is dead. Firestar tried her best to block out everything Spider-man was saying and Venom was saying, but she stops right when Kasady was about to die. Venom is then furious and attacks Firestar, but Spider-man gets in his way so Venom smacks him away. Shortly after Carnage is fully healed and he then gets Shriek to use her Sonic bursts to defeat Venom. They later bring Venom off to find a place where they can torture him. description: The Stormwatch headquarters is invaded by a squad of people who are intent on killing Battalion. After Stormwatch disposes of them, Battalion thinks back on the first Stormwatch team and how young they were at the time. They stopped a group from kidnapping some scientists and Battalion used his psionic abilities to disable one of the gang, giving him permanent mental damage. That gang member's brother was the one that invaded the Stormwatch facility in the present and wanted to kill Battalion.

What do women want? Archer is about to find out the hard way, when Armstrong sets him up on his first date! Of course, when you're a highly trained assassin who's spent most of his life in monastery, things are bound to get awkward-- and deadly!

Bloodshot has traced the Weaponeer hijackings to Harbinger mercenaries Cinder and Glyder. But can even Bloodshot's nanite-filled blood save him when he goes skydiving without a parachute? Even if he does he'll still have Ninjak to contend with!

First appearance Ninjak in costume!

The Immortal Enemy has taken over the body of Gilad Anni-Padda! The now desperate Geomancer, Geoff McHenry, will have to enlist the help of some old and trusted allies to stop this ages old evil the only way they can-- by killing the Eternal Warrior!

Our hero's immortal body-swapping enemy takes him over! Will the Geomancer survive?

description:
While Flatline and Superstar search L.A. for flatline's lost love, Virgil gets some much-needed downtime with his daughter in Colorado. When things go haywire, they'll need a little extra help to save the day.

The Corps is recruited to protect a vital witness in a criminal case. The criminals attack en masse inside an amusement park.

description: Trapped. Isolated. Defeated. Peter Stanchek lies broken in the dungeons of Kaliph's Iranian fortress without any of hope of escape. It's up to his allies and new recruit Screen to mount a rescue, but with each moment they waste, the more Kaliph breaks Peter's spirit. The race is on to save the resistance's most powerful member!

description:
While continuing his battle with the technological-enhanced dinosaurs, Turok forms an uneasy alliance with a South American drug lord and obtains superior weapons.

Alone again Turok roams a South American jungle hunting Mon-Ark's dinosaurs. His time here has brought him the attention of Carlos Comacho. Carlos is a Drug Lord whose business is going down quickly thanks to the dinosaurs that are killing and eating his men. Hearing about Turok he seeks him out and supplies him with his best weapons to kill the beasts. Turok uneasy of Carlos offer accepts.

Turok also runs into a woman named Maria Cortez who wants Turok to capture these dinosaurs alive to breed them for science. Turok refuses and eventually in a climatic conclusion Turok fights and kills the mate of Mon-Ark with Carols weapons only to find out from Maria that despite his help the mate of Mon-Ark has already laid a brood of eggs and they are going to reproduce without Turok's help.
name: Lizards Of The Night

description:
To save Randy's life, Aric must surrender the X-O armor! Trapped in a prison deep within Antarctica, Aric and Randy will have to escape before the good skin turns bad. But even if they can break free, there's no avoiding the deadly polar deep freeze!

1st appearance:

- Dr. Philip Zahn

- Armorines

description:
This issue features a classic John Bolton tale of playful prehistoric parody, as well as an all-new "Stan Pulsar" yarn of space pirates and sunken treasure by Cailleteau & Vatine. Michael Cherkas, Larry Hancock, and John van Bruggen continue the crescendo of murder, mystery, and mayhem in "Suburban Nightmares: Secrets," while Cossu & Jamsin flirt with the fine-edged follies of human motivation in "The Art Opening." In "Post-Apocalypse," Phil Elliott and Lloyd Thatcher extol the ecstasies of toxic waste, and Nicole Hollander's "Sylvia" teams up with "Clyde, Domestic Scientist" to investigate the commercial possibilities of zucchini plants. Exciting painted and mixed-media cover by John K. Snyder.

Story Titles

  • Sylvia
  • Stan Pulsar
  • Post-Apocalypse
  • Suburban Nightmares: Secrets Chapter 4
  • Fighting Words
  • The Art Opening

Continuing with Dark Horse's popular reprint series, this issue Luke Skywalker encounters a menacing Darth Vader at the Iron Tower on Aridus, and a new friend posing as an old one gives his life to save Luke and the natives of Aridus from Vader's treachery. Meanwhile, a Rebel scheme for destroying Vader's private cruiser unfolds, with the legendary power gems of the pirates of Iridium holding the key. Han Solo and Chewbacca volunteer to retrieve the gem, but don't count on being thrown to the wolves in the bargain!
name: The Return of Ben Kenobi (part 2), The Power Gem (part 1)

description:
What happens when an irresistible force comes in contact with an immovable object? What happens when two of the mightiest mythological entities of all time clash in mortal combat? Find out in "When Immortals Meet," the first chapter in the knock-down, drag-out battle of the year: Eddie Campbell's Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid! Also: Alien life forms are duped into signing away their own planet in the conclusion of Charles Moore and Andrew Robinson's The Chairman, and film and comics legends Alexandro Jodorowsky and Moebius wrap up their tale of "The Madwoman of the Sacred Heart." Special homage cover by Campbell.

Chapters

  • Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid - Part 1 (of 9), "Place Your Bets."
  • The Chairman - Part 3 (of 3)
  • The Madwoman of the Sacred Heart - Part 7 (of 7)
name: Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid; The Chairman; The Madwoman of the Sacred Heart

description:
With his plans in motion and his true nature still unknown by the citizens of Earth, Cyborg Superman prepares to take out Superboy! Does the Boy of Steel have any chance of surviving a fight with a killer who still claims to be the real Superman?! Meanwhile, a Kryptonian Battle Suit is fired up at Superman's Fortress of Solitude--who's inside?!

Issue Tagline: Don't Send a Boy to Do a Man's Job!

Notes:

  • Chronological continuation from Superman #80.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #690.

With Batman down, Bane began attacking and absorbing gangs across Gotham City. Dr. Kinsolving was asked to be Bruce Wayne's personal doctor for the immediate future while he recovered from his "car accident." Bane's crew caught Catwoman; she was asked to pay Bane tribute. With Bruce's blessing, Tim asked Jean Paul to fill in as Batman.

Heat, Part 3 of 4. Catman's murderous spree continues as the heat wave holds Gotham City at its mercy. Batman and Catwoman form an uneasy alliance to bring down the increasingly unpredictable killer, leading to a three-way confrontation at the Gotham Zoo...until an enraged black panther makes it a foursome!

Notes:

  • Cover dated Early August 1993.

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Part 1 of 8. It's a sprawling cosmic saga as the stars of GREEN LANTERN, L.E.G.I.O.N. '93 and THE DARKSTARS come together in one of the greatest space adventures ever: DC UNIVERSE: TRINITY, a crossover in 8 parts that decides, once and for all, who has jurisdiction over the spaceways. TRINITY is the story of the Triarch, a trio of ancient deities who, a billion years ago, attempted to remake the universe. Now they're returned to finish the job, forcing the Green Lantern Corps, L.E.G.I.O.N. and the Darkstars into a cataclysmic war with seemingly omnipotent beings. Continues in Green Lantern (1990 2nd Series) #44.

description: He's the Identity Addict and he can't stop changing identities, so the Doom Patrol beat their way to his doorstep only to meet the Visionary Stomach, the Unborn Peacock, the Compassionate Cop and the Better Mousetrap.
name: Down Among The Underpinnings

description:
Wally finds out everything about the so called Barry Allen, but what will Wally do about it?

Wally West has proven that Professor Zoom is the fake Barry Allen, but the Zoom that faces Wally now is not the same man that killed Iris. Eobard reveals that he is from the future and that he saw Barry as a hero and even had surgery to look like Barry and stole the Cosmic Treadmill. He then gave himself super speed and came the the 20th century to meet Barry Allen. But something went wrong and he arrived years after Barry's death. He went to the Flash Museum where he learned that he was going to become the man that killed Iris and was going to be killed by Barry. Eobard went crazy and thought that he was Barry Allen. When he remembered who he was he deduced the only way to survive was to stay in the present and become Barry Allen.

Eobard is about to kill Wally when Max Mercury, Johnny Quick and Hal Jordan arrive and force Eobard to run away. They take Wally to the hospital where Jay Garrick is laid up. Then they see on the news that Eobard is attacking Linda and Wally rushes off to save her. This time beats Wally up and forces him to chase after. But Wally has a plan and tricks Eobard into thinking that he used the treadmill to kill Eobard as a baby.

Eobard uses the treadmill to stop Wally but is launched into the future with no memory of where he was and Wally reveals he just hid.

Epilogue: The book The Life of Barry Allen was written by Iris Allen three years later.
name: The Once and Future Flash

description: Trinity: Part 2. "Urban Renewal!" Guest-starring Lobo and L.E.G.I.O.N. Story continued from DC Universe: Trinity (1993) #1. In order to stop the whole scale destruction of Maltus, Hal will have to defy the Guardians and crossover into L.E.G..I.O.N. jurisdiction. But it only took one Triach to defeat him before, how can Green Lantern hope to defeat three?! Story continues in L.E.G.I.O.N. (1989-1994 1st Series)
name: Urban Renewal

description: With the spirit of Ch'p as his guide, Green Lantern John Stewart descends into his own personal hell to confront all the people he's killed throughout his life...including, at the center of his deepest circles, his dead wife, Katma Tui.
name: What Dis Be

description: Heartbroken and homeless, Constantine has nothing left to do except crawl inside a bottle. Unfortunately for the chain-smoking hero, he isn't the only one in need of a drink: the King of the Vampires returns looking to quench his own thirst!
name: Down All the Days

description:
A trio of brutes ambush Jonah Hex and prepare to hang him from a tree tied to his horse. They want revenge upon Hex for killing their sister. But an old timer named Slow Go Smith appears and shoots the brothers down and frees Hex. Slow Go is a bounty hunter and is preparing to take the brothers to Mud Creek so he can cash in the reward. He cuts their heads off to make transportation (and proof of identity) easier. Jonah decides to come with him.

When Jonah and Slow Go arrive in Mud Creek, they find a con artist offering to snap photographs of people standing next to the corpses of dead famous outlaws for a nickel. The problem being - none of the outlaws he features are in fact the genuine article.

Jonah and Slow Go rent a room for the night, but Jonah kicks Slow Go into the barn because of his loud snoring. Inside the barn are the bodies of the Price Gang, another notorious gang of outlaws. Slow Go tries to fall asleep, but is awakened when he hears a noise coming from nearby. The body of one of the Price Brothers is standing upright holding a six-gun.

Jonah awakens to the report of shots being fired, coming from the barn. He leaps out of his window to investigate the issue.
name: Slow Go Smith

description: The Justice League lands in the middle of a civil war when they head south to secure an international air strip on Seylone Island, forcing them to go head to head against an entire army and interfere in international affairs. Â
name: Lives in the Balance

description: Elongated Man and Tasmanian Devil are in Africa on the trail of a fantastic creature, while Crimson Fox makes a shocking discovery in London...her long-dead husband is alive! But their surprising reunion turns tragic when he's revealed to be a super-villain! Â
name: Deadly Liaisons

description: Part 3 of the 3-part 'The Tyranny Gun.' With rebels preparing for all-out war, Blitz faces off against the combined might of Martian Manhunter and his Task Force while the seconds tick away to the moment when the Ultimate Weapon will destroy half the Caribbean. Â
name: Twisted Glass!

description: It's a road trip for the Kid, who, in typical fashion, drives right into a race riot.
name: Krumville 50

description: Dislodged from the present, Pat takes shelter in memories of Myrwann's past - the years he spent in Hollywood working with Chaplin and Keaton on silent screen gems. But utilizing comedy as a survival technique proves costly for Myrwann (in the past) and Pat (in the present). Â
name: A Memorable Fancy

description:
Even as the team battles against resurrected Legionnaires to save the galaxy, intense personal conflicts arise between Karate Kid and Projectra, and Cosmic Boy and his dead brother, Magnetic Kid.

Mordru unleashes the corpses of the dead Legionnaires as his army of undead continue to assault the Legion.

The reborn Fatal Five is out for blood...and not just the Legionnaires'. They want the man who reunited them as well.

The Fatal Five get in a conflict against the Legion of Super-Heroes while they hold the Vice-President of the United Planets hostage.
name: New Life, New Death!

description: Metamorpho, former member of the Outsiders and of the Justice League, cuts loose with the strange powers at his command in a 4-issue miniseries that returns him to his roots as a world-renowned soldier of fortune. This time, though, the stakes are higher than ever, as Rex Mason embarks on a quest to save the life of his infant son. Even as the Element Man clashes with angry natives, deadly traps, certain death and a confrontation with his tortured past, the story also delves into his relationships with his child, his ex-wife Sapphire and her brutish husband Java. Shocking discoveries redefine Metamorpho's life and set the stage for a very different future.Â
name: Like Father Like Son

description: A new murderer makes his mark and Wesley Dodds must again don his mask or confront dark dreams in this first part of a new storyline. The mysterious villain the Face takes only heads and the Chinatown gangs will take to the streets if the Golden Age Sandman doesn't find the killer first.
name: The Face: Act One

description:
The ZERO HOUR tie-in continues as another traveler--and familiar face--tells their tale. The Faerie Cluracan heads to Aurelian during a political upheaval and ends up causing an uproar of his own! "World's End" part 2.

Cluracan of Faerie tells a tale of a journey he made, before he got to the Worlds End. It includes Morpheus, an evil man and many other things.

Outer story (pgs 1, 2, 25):

Penciller: Bryan Talbot

Inker: Mark Buckingham

Inner story (pgs 3-24):

Penciller/Inker: John Watkiss
name: Worlds' End, Part 2: Cluracan's Tale

description: Check into the Hotel Shade and be prepared for a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Hallucinations plague the proprietors, Shade, Kathy and Lenny, when one of their guests checks in to begin "The Great American Novel."
name: The Great American Novel

description: Saavik is forced to pay the price when she must capture a Starfleet defector in Romulan space before he can deliver crucial military secrets to the enemy.
name: Renegade

description: The Worst of Both Worlds, Part 3 of 4. The away team and the Borg battle over Locutus within the ruins of Starfleet Headquarters...with Picard's soul the ultimate prize!
name: The Armies of the Night

description: Arcane takes possession of the Sunderland empire; Swamp Thing's marriage with Abby reaches a crossroads; and a surprise guest star returns.
name: She's Leaving Houma

description:
This comic book is Issue #5 of the series "1963". It involves the character. "Horus, Lord of Light", as he has dealings with other Egyptian mythological beings and deities from his realm. He utilizes a human guise as a Professor of Egyptology, and it is during this guise one of his students accidentally gets caught up with Horus when he transforms from his human guise back to his superhero identity. The female student soon decides to stow away on Horus' "day vessel" as one of his duties is to steer it through the nethers so Earth and the Sun can experience the transition from night to day to prevent other deities like Anubis from taking over the Earth and the cosmos should the vessel fail.

Horus soon encounters the ensemble of Egyptian deities after it is discovered the "mere mortal", the College student, has stowed away on the vessel, but had effectively steered the ship while Horus had battles with Anubis and other creatures.

The comic is written as analogous to Thor from Marvel, with over the top "myth speak" and a Jack Kirby-esque art style. Jabs are even made at the treatment of women, revealing a type of overt machismo of not only the arrogant deities but of some people during this time period.

The back pages feature a phony letters page as well as a sketch gallery of a few "1963" characters.
name: Twelve Hours To Dawn!

description:
John Lynch regrets killing so many people during his life as a merc, but finds himself pulled back into the shadowy world of his past when he discovers a terrible problem that requires his expertise.

John Lynch started to regret killing so many people in his life as a merc. He soon founs out he had a terrible problem. Would he take on his last mission or will he be dead by dawn?

Mighty Man rescues Dart and Star from a battle during a jailbreak. Dragon and Alex Wilde conclude that Lt. Darling is corrupt. SkullFace threatens Darling's family. The Fiend unsuccessfully attacks Dragon. Police find the dead couple in DeKalb.

Spawn infiltrates the YoungBlood head quarters with his mind set on vengeance. He has found his killer, and won't stop 'till he even's the score. Eventually Spawn gets a chance to fight his target one on one, in some desolate area (Due to his teleportation abilities). Spawn brutally beats his enemy to a pulp, and just before Spawn returns home, he leaves his enemy with a painful little gift.
name: Flashback Pt.2

description: Some Daemonites arrive near the Stormwatch headquarters and are able to possess the bodies of some Stormwatch personnel. They infiltrate the headquarters in the hopes of releasing the Warguard, a trio of super-powered beings that have been placed in a cryogenic chamber in the headquarters. A team of Stormwatch members arrive too late to prevent the Warguard being released and they are prepared for a massive battle to erupt.

name: Khrome the Conqueror

description: A high school student named Amber Hunt is one of the most popular girls in her school and very spoiled. In the middle of her biology class, Amber Hunt and the rest of her classmates find that a battle between ultras, people with super-human powers, is going on right outside of their school. To Amber Hunt's surprise, she finds that both factions of ultras are fighting over her. The winner of the fight, the Exiles, gather Amber Hunt before she can escape and they take her to their secret headquarters: an island off the coast of California. There she meets Doctor Rachel Deming, who explains that the Exiles saved Amber from certain death. Meanwhile, the Supreme Soviet informs Malcolm Kort, the man who hired him to capture Amber Hunt, that he has failed. Supreme Soviet still demands payment and Kort introduces him to Hot Rox, a powerful ultra. Hot Rox places Supreme Soviet in a holding tank that exposes him to an mRNA gene therapy that would give people with the Theta virus a super power, but kills those without it. Since Supreme Soviet is only human, it effectively killed him. Meanwhile, another contingent of the Exiles, Catapult and Mustang, goes on a mission to gather another potential person with the Theta virus, Timothy Halloran. There they are met with Bruut and Bloodbath, two agents also trying to get Timothy Halloran. A fight ensues and Timothy's mother becomes a fatality. Bruut is also taken down, but Bloodbath is able to escape with Timothy.
name: Exiles

description: The Freex first meeting ends in fights and arguments. Pressure leaves and is confronted by police officers. Before they can arrest her or she can resist, a person named Rush runs by and grabs her. Rush, an ultra with the ability of super speed, informs Pressure that she could use her powers for money, even if it may be breaking the law. Meanwhile, the other members of Freex try to come to terms with their situation while some of them reflect on their origins. While Rush brings Pressure to a place where they'll be enforcers for loan sharks for money, they stop at a television broadcasting Captain Jacob Rome. Captain Rome is the man in charge of the police case involving the members of the Freex. Rush reveals to Pressure that Captain Rome is his father. The police surround the Freex in an abandoned building and they try to figure a way to escape.
name: Blown Apart

description: Choice is still with Hardcase and that makes the president of the Choice Corporation very nervous. He is counseled by J.D. Hunt and Rex Mundi. Rex Mundi decides to send the Omega Team, a group of mercenaries, to recapture Choice. Meanwhile, Hardcase and Choice are at Hardcase's home speaking with Detective Brown about the events that transpired earlier that day. When the media arrives, Hardcase and Choice leave the house and head to the beach. It's there that the Omega Team attacks, but they are eventually defeated. Tired, Hardcase and Choice return to Hardcase's home to find that the Strangers are there waiting for him.
name: Hard Decisions

description: Miss Fury battles against the combined might of the Cat Pack on her own, in an abandoned mall, in order to free the President's grandson from her foe, Black Fury. She surrenders to the Cat Pack, telling them to take her to their leader. She carries a hidden communicator with her that allows the Protectors to track her down to Black Fury's secret hideout. The Protectors wait outside of the abandoned mall, waiting for Miss Fury's code word for them to attack. Miss Fury arrives in front of Black Fury and she accuses of her of being her aunt Stephanie. Black Fury says she has no idea what she is talking about and Miss Fury is left with doubt. While the Protectors remain to wait for Miss Fury's code word, they see the Arrow enter the abandoned mall. He figures that if he saves the President's grandson alone, the Protectors would have no choice but to accept him as a member. Amazing Man realizes they have no choice and orders Air Man to drop Aura into the mall. Aura falls down, protected by her force field, and is able to save the President's grandson, holding him in her field. The Protectors burst into the building and Black Fury sends her Cat Pack against them as she tries to flee. While the Protectors defeat the Cat Pack, Miss Fury chases Black Fury. Black Fury brandishes a gun against her niece and almost shot her if it were not for the intervention of a well placed shot by the Arrow. Black Fury then detonates a bomb that will destroy the building. Miss Fury lets Black Fury get away, more concerned for getting everyone out of there. With the Protectors safe, they offer Miss Fury membership, but she has to decline. The Arrow gets angry that they did not ask him to join and he storms off. Meanwhile, in another dimesnion, an alien tyrant named Extreme takes over the planet and vows to capture all planets and make them his.
name: Hell Hath No Fury

description: The original Prototype, Bob Campbell, was permanently disfigured in an exhibition with Prototype 2000. He lost his arm in the battle. Ultra Tech, the company that created the Prototype power suit as well as Prototype 2000, fired Bob Campbell and went on to make a stronger Prototype armor. A new person is hired to control the new Prototype, Jimmy Ruiz. Ultra Tech unveils the new armor in an exhibition for the company shareholders when an ultra named Glare begins causing a rampage in the streets, searching for the president of Ultra Tech: Stanley Leland. Mr. Leland sends Prototype to fight Glare, mostly for the publicity, and the two fight. The battle is fierce and fast paced and it seems Prototype accidentally killed Glare in the heat of the moment.
name: Budget Cuts

description: The Strangers face J.D. Hunt's hired guns, TNTNT.
name: TNTNT
